    <title type="text">Open Access Journal: VATES</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<span style="font-size: xx-small;">[First posted in AWOL 3 August
      2011. Updated 30 August 2013]</span><br /><br /><a
      href="http://pineapplepubs.snazzystuff.co.uk/vates.htm">VATES: The Journal of New Latin
      Poetry</a><br /><blockquote><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"><span style="color: purple; font-size:
      x-small;"><b>VATES</b></span></span><span style="font-family:
      Bookman Old Style; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;">
      </span>is an </span><span style="font-family: Bookman Old Style; font-size:
      x-small;">occasional publication that aims to bring contemporary Latin poetry to the
      attention of an English-speaking audience. The purpose of the journal is to promote both the
      reading and the writing of new Latin verse in an attempt to reverse the decline of Latin poetry
      composition in the English-speaking world.</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
      </span></blockquote><blockquote><span style="font-family: Bookman Old
      Style; font-size: x-small;">Published electronically in pdf format, the journal is sent
      <u>free of charge</u> to any individual or organisation who wishes to see it. They
      in turn are encouraged to circulate it – either electronically or by printing copies – to an
      even wider audience. The hope is that the very existence of such a forum for the dissemination
      of Latin verse will encourage readers to contribute.</span> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span></blockquote><blockquote><span
      style="font-family: Bookman Old Style; font-size: x-small;">The journal is not 'academic' in
      tone: it is intended for anyone with an interest in the subject. In order to make the
      publication as accessible as possible, featured Latin poems are accompanied by English
      translations and all editorial articles are in English.</span> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span></blockquote><blockquote><div
      class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Bookman Old Style; font-size:
      x-small;">The journal also features articles on the history of the genre and hints and tips
      about writing Latin poetry.</span></div></blockquote><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"><span style="color: purple; font-size: x-small;">* <a
      href="http://pineapplepubs.snazzystuff.co.uk/Vates%20issue%208.pdf"><b>Vates 8
      </b></a>(Autumn 2013) *&nbsp;</span></span> <br /><span
      style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><b><span
      style="color: purple;">* <a
      href="http://pineapplepubs.snazzystuff.co.uk/Vates%20issue%207.pdf"> Vates 7</a>
      (Spring 2013) *&nbsp;</span></b></span></span> <br /><span
